{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide free access to public swimming pools for children under the age of six.",
        "additional_details": "Swimming is a life-saving skill that every child should have the chance to learn. The cost of weekly 60-minute swim sessions for two children and two adults is significant and can be a barrier for many families. \r\n\r\nThe Government should fund indoor swimming up to age 6 to remove financial obstacles and ensure equal access. It should also require all venues offering children\u2019s swim lessons to be registered with the Tax-Free Childcare scheme.",
        "background": "Subsidise or fully fund indoor swimming for all children up to age 6. Many pools already offer free entry for under-2s, but free access beyond that varies. Government support would ensure every child can learn to swim early, giving them a vital life skill and improving water safety nationwide.",
